# **Key Registry (Composite Join Surface)**

**Goal:** one tiny, authoritative table that maps every funding/program record to the same canonical keys so SAM.gov, USAspending, and Arkansas DFA/agency exports snap together without hand‚Äëfixes.

## **Why this matters (plain English)**

* Different sources name the same thing differently. A composite key prevents drift and duplicate entities.  
* Once in place, every new dataset ‚Äúplugs in‚Äù to CLE/WELL with zero manual reconciliation.  
* It becomes your universal `JOIN ... USING (...)` surface across money flows, authority refs, and field validations.

## **Minimal columns (v1)**

* `entity_name` (normalized legal name)  
* `uei` (Unique Entity Identifier)  
* `ein` (Employer Identification Number)  
* `assistance_listing` (CFDA/AL number, e.g., `93.958`)  
* `state_fund_code` (Arkansas internal code/key used in DFA/agency ledgers)  
* `duns_legacy` (nullable; legacy link if it appears in older files)  
* `aka_names` (array/text for common variants)  
* `status` (active | retired)  
* `source_of_truth` (who last validated it)  
* `valid_from`, `valid_to` (temporal bounds)

## **Storage formats**

* **Authoritative CSV** for quick joins  
* **YAML** shadow file for CLE/WELL lineage (editor \+ timestamps)  
* Optional **SQLite/Parquet** for fast local analytics

## **v1 YAML record (example)**

`- entity_name: "NAMI Arkansas, Inc."`  
  `uei: "ABCDEFG12345"`  
  `ein: "71-0XXXXX9"`  
  `assistance_listing: ["93.958", "16.585"]`  
  `state_fund_code: ["AOC-SPC-ACCT", "DHS-DAABHS-GR"]`  
  `duns_legacy: null`  
  `aka_names: ["NAMI AR", "National Alliance on Mental Illness - Arkansas"]`  
  `status: active`  
  `source_of_truth: "Editor: Vera ‚Ä¢ Evidence: USAspending/SAM.gov/DFA"`  
  `valid_from: "2024-07-01"`  
  `valid_to: null`

## **Normalization rules (keep it boring & strict)**

* Uppercase for codes (`UEI`, AL/CFDA, fund codes), title case for names.  
* Strip punctuation/Inc./LLC from `entity_name` but keep the legal form in a separate field if needed.  
* AL/CFDA must be `NN.NNN` string form.  
* `state_fund_code` must be the exact code used in Arkansas ledgers (no ‚Äúfriendly‚Äù labels).

## **How to use it (joins that just work)**

* **SAM.gov ‚Üí** join on `uei`  
* **USAspending ‚Üí** join on `uei` or `assistance_listing` (plus year, if needed)  
* **Arkansas DFA/agency ledgers ‚Üí** join on `state_fund_code` (and fiscal year)  
* **Legacy files ‚Üí** fallback to `duns_legacy` or `ein` with name‚Äësimilarity as a last step

## **SQL sketch (SQLite/Postgres)**

`CREATE TABLE key_registry (`  
  `entity_name TEXT NOT NULL,`  
  `uei TEXT,`  
  `ein TEXT,`  
  `assistance_listing TEXT[],     -- or TEXT with comma‚Äësep in SQLite`  
  `state_fund_code TEXT[],`  
  `duns_legacy TEXT,`  
  `aka_names TEXT[],`  
  `status TEXT CHECK (status IN ('active','retired')) DEFAULT 'active',`  
  `source_of_truth TEXT,`  
  `valid_from DATE,`  
  `valid_to DATE`  
`);`

`-- Example composite view for easy joins`  
`CREATE VIEW join_surface AS`  
`SELECT`  
  `entity_name,`  
  `uei,`  
  `ein,`  
  `unnest(assistance_listing) AS assistance_listing,`  
  `unnest(state_fund_code)    AS state_fund_code`  
`FROM key_registry`  
`WHERE status='active';`

## **3\) Gap Classification Rules (What to Follow Up vs Ignore)**

### **Gap Classes (assign one per gap)**

| GAP\_CLASS | Definition (facts-only) | Typical Cause | Next Action |

| G0-NO-KEYS | Record contains no joinable keys (no UEI, no fund code, no AL) | Source is narrative-only | Extract verbatim identifiers; keep as implementation evidence only |
| G1-NO-STATE-CROSSWALK | Federal record exists but no state fund code link | State routing not published in that dataset | Search DFA/agency docs for pass-through / subaward references |
| G2-NO-FEDERAL-ID | State fund code exists but no UEI/AL mapping | State ledger doesn‚Äôt carry federal IDs | Add registry mapping when an authoritative crosswalk appears |
| G3-NO-AUTHORITY | Money exists but no authority citation captured | Authority doc not collected yet | Collect the governing statute/order/rule for that fund/program |
| G4-NO-IMPLEMENTATION | Money/authority exist but no program execution proof | Program docs not collected yet | Collect DHS division program page, RFP, grant manual, reporting instructions |
| G5-NO-OVERSIGHT | Money/implementation exist but no oversight artifact | Oversight is elsewhere (audit, committee, reporting) | Look for audit reports, legislative oversight references, reporting requirements |
| G6-CONFLICT | Two sources disagree on same field (amount/name/owner) | Reporting lag or different scopes | Keep both as separate evidence items; mark conflict for later resolution |
| G7-STALE | Source is older than current fiscal context | Publication lag | Keep but time-bound; do not project forward |
| G8-UNSCOPED | Record is not DHS-touch plausible | Out-of-lane capture | Park it; do not spend cycles unless later connected by a join |
